<subSubSection lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="41" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
In the Spinola collection, two specimens from Egypt (D. Waltl) and South Africa (Cap B. [onne] Esp. [
<normalizedToken originalValue="érance">erance</normalizedToken>
]&quot; (D. Klug)) referring to this species are present. Only one specimen belongs to the original type series. However, it is currently impossible to state which one, since both specimens lack locality labels. At present, we cannot identify the specimen that had been collected in Egypt. Both specimens were examined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Nicolai, Berlin" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" title="Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis, specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per familias, genera, species et varietates disposita atque descripta ab Adrea Gustavo Dahlbom. Chrysis in sensu Linneano" year="1854">Dahlbom (1854</bibRefCitation>
: 60) and they are found under the name &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum coelestinum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coelestinum">
<pageBreakToken pageId="41" pageNumber="42" start="start">Hedychrum</pageBreakToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="cœlestinum">coelestinum</normalizedToken>
</taxonomicName>
Kl.&quot;, a species never described by Klug. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Nicolai, Berlin" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" title="Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis, specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per familias, genera, species et varietates disposita atque descripta ab Adrea Gustavo Dahlbom. Chrysis in sensu Linneano" year="1854">Dahlbom (1854)</bibRefCitation>
erroneusly assigned this species to Klug and not to Spinola, even though he knew 
<bibRefCitation author="Spinola, M" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="437 - 546" title="Comte rendu des Hymenopteres recuillis par M. Fischer pendant son voyage en Egypte, et communiques par M. le Docteur Waltl a Maximilien Spinola." volume="7" year="1838">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Spinola’s">Spinola's</normalizedToken>
(1838)
</bibRefCitation>
paper. Furthermore, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Nicolai, Berlin" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" title="Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis, specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per familias, genera, species et varietates disposita atque descripta ab Adrea Gustavo Dahlbom. Chrysis in sensu Linneano" year="1854">Dahlbom (1854)</bibRefCitation>
named this species &quot; 
<taxonomicName lsidName="caelestinum" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" rank="species" species="caelestinum">caelestinum</taxonomicName>
&quot;, which we consider an incorrect subsequent spelling (
<bibRefCitation author="Madl, M" journalOrPublisher="Linzer Biologische Beitraege" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="5 - 169" title="A Catalogue of the Chrysididae (Hymenoptera: Chrysidoidea) of the Ethiopian Region excluding Malagasy Subregion." volume="44" year="2012">Madl and Rosa 2012</bibRefCitation>
: 96). The two specimens were labelled as lectotype and paralectotype by L.D. French, but the lectotype designation has not been published. The two females have different colours: one is greenish and the second is a deep blue. The blue one was labelled by French as paralectotype, but the colour matches 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Spinola’s">Spinola's</normalizedToken>
description (&quot;La couleur du corps est 
<normalizedToken originalValue="d’un">d'un</normalizedToken>
bleu plus intense&quot;) and we suppose that this one could be the type. In 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Dahlbom’s">Dahlbom's</normalizedToken>
collection in LZM, there is another specimen labelled as type by a former curator, not by Dahlbom himself, and that refers to the specimen listed as &quot; 
<taxonomicName lsidName="caelestinum" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" rank="species" species="caelestinum">caelestinum</taxonomicName>
Kl.&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="Dahlbom, AG" journalOrPublisher="Nicolai, Berlin" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" title="Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue Borealia, formis typicis nonnullis, specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per familias, genera, species et varietates disposita atque descripta ab Adrea Gustavo Dahlbom. Chrysis in sensu Linneano" year="1854">Dahlbom 1854</bibRefCitation>
: 60).
</paragraph>
